HEADWORD: Plastin
<hw>Plas"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to form,
mold.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A substance associated with nuclein
in cell nuclei, and by some considered as the fundamental substance of
the nucleus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

